    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with high-ceiling opportunities, anchored by **Kyle Tucker** (77.26) and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (73.66). **Kyle Tucker** stands as our premier play; despite a 35% rain risk in his matchup against Landen Roupp, his elite xwOBA (.372) and favorable wind conditions outweigh the volatility. Similarly, **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** benefits from a massive matchup grade against the high-xERA arm of Reynaldo L\u00f3pez (6.36), with his dynamic platoon advantage and batting order stability making him a near-lock for production. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (71.68) and **Jackson Merrill** (70.92) also provide high-floor output, with the latter benefiting from a +14% park factor, positioning our top-tier talent to exploit today\u2019s most vulnerable pitching rotations.\n\nWhile our confidence is high, the optimizer remains cautious regarding stolen base scarcity and weather. **Andy Pages** (61.82) earns a spot due to his wind-aided power profile, but remains a monitor-heavy start due to the 35% rain risk and the presence of an elite defensive catcher. The most difficult bench decision involved **Marcell Ozuna** (52.65), who missed the cut by less than a point. While **Marcell Ozuna** carries strong base projections, the optimizer favored the positional utility and specific lineup-order advantages of **Liam Hicks** and **Drake Baldwin** to ensure our catcher slots remain efficient. We are also keeping a close eye on **Gunnar Henderson**; while he is a staple of our offense, his score (56.78) was tempered by a significant platoon hit (-15%) against the southpaw Kris Bubic, though the combination of batting leadoff and favorable wind keeps him in the starting lineup over bench options like **Coby Mayo** (51.14) or **Jacob Wilson** (49.33).",
